{
  "texts": [
    "Training a single model has space complex- ity O(p), where p ∶= | |; this complexity scales linearly with the number of models trained in parallel.",
    "Table 1 treats the level of training concurrency as a constant factor, which is why LOO's total space complexity is listed as O(n + p).",
    "A naive implementation of LOO would train the n additional models and immediately discard them after measuring z te 's test loss.",
    "This simple version of LOO has O(1) storage complexity.",
    "If instead the (n + 1) models are stored, analysis of subsequent test instances requires no additional retraining."
  ]
}